8 A Concurrent Resolution honoring the 50th anniversary
of the Fall of Saigon and end of the Vietnam War;
9 recognizing the subsequent growth of the Vietnamese
American community, culture, and economic impact in
10 Oklahoma; and celebrating those who fought for the
freedom of Vietnam and Vietnamese American citizens.
11
12
13 WHEREAS, April 30, 2025, marks the 50th anniversary of the Fall
14 of Saigon, a pivotal moment in world history which marked the end of
15 the Vietnam War and led to mass displacement of millions of
16 Vietnamese refugees; and
17 WHEREAS, many Vietnamese families fled their homeland in search
18 of freedom, safety, and opportunity, enduring perilous journeys and
19 resettling in countries around the world, including the United
20 States; and
21 WHEREAS, the State of Oklahoma became home to a vibrant
22 Vietnamese American community that has enriched the state's
23 cultural, economic, and social landscape over the past five decades;
24 and
