5 WHEREAS, Vietnamese Americans in Oklahoma have made lasting
6 contributions as entrepreneurs, educators, medical professionals,
7 public servants, faith leaders, and community advocates; and
8 WHEREAS, cultural celebrations such as Tet (Vietnamese Lunar New
9 Year) and the preservation of Vietnamese heritage have strengthened
10 Oklahoma's multicultural identity and promoted cross-cultural
11 understanding; and
12 WHEREAS, this 50th anniversary provides an opportunity for all
13 Oklahomans to reflect on the tragic costs of war, the power of
14 perseverance, and the enduring values of freedom and democracy; and
15 WHEREAS, in honoring and recognizing our Vietnamese American
16 Community, the State of Oklahoma continues to recognize the South
17 Republic Heritage flag (yellow flag with three red stripes) as the
18 official flag to honor those who have fought for the freedom of
19 Vietnam and our fellow Vietnamese American citizens of the State of
20 Oklahoma; and
